column11: Ratings given were largely based on how fast the images load and how long it actually took for the entire page to finish loading. As for the guideline, 1 or 2 video examples to show what constitutes a bad or excellent rating would be helpful.
how long it took for everything to load

The first two felt like it was hooked up to an old DSL line; parts would load, then other parts would load. The second one looked especially bad, having the second set of content load in between the staggered ones looked more like a bad connection. The third one looked how I expected it to.
experiment guideline was clear and i had rated based on the website page load
Guidelines was very clear. Three videos loading speed was different. So all videos get different ratings, like strongly agree, agree and neutral. There was no confused about grading process.
pages opening part by part is like waiting more time
Loading of third line is slow.  Fourth line also loads slowly.  Guideline is clear.
loading webpage is most importand. The guideline is clear.
Well, the first two just took way too long. The 3rd one had eveything loaded instantly.
The time taken to load the webpage is the reason for grading.
The last video loaded quickly and all at once. The first two visits were fairly quick but did not load at once.
